        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Curacao</placeName>
                <date>26<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Oct. 1848</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Mr. I Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>!</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Dear Friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">I recd your Sundry<lb/> forms <date>2d March</date>
                <date>2d May</date> and <date>31 Aug</date> together with all the missing<lb/>
                Occidents and a letter <add>from Mr</add>
                <persName>I J Seixas</persName> explaining the detentions of<lb/> these letters and
                books having been <sic>occassined</sic> by the negligence<lb/> of your
                    <placeName>New York</placeName> Agent, which I regret as it has been the<lb/>
                cause of my losing many Subscribers, I was reduced to 5<lb/> but since the books
                have arrived I have got 2 more thus<lb/> nowI have 7 Subscribers, in my last I
                informed you<lb/> of having disposed of One Sett of prayer Books since which<lb/>
                tho we have passed all the <sic>Hollidays</sic> which in the time to<lb/> sell I
                have not been able to <add>?</add> of a single sett. They<lb/> all complain the
                Books are too large &amp; heavy so much so<lb/> that I have orders for three setts
                of printed on thin paper<lb/> like your daily services, and as they fear you will
                not have<lb/> them bound as they wish, <hi rend="underline">that is to say One of
                    the <add>?</add></hi>, he<lb/> requests you will send him out, an <hi
                    rend="underline">unbound</hi> Sett if on <hi rend="underline">thin</hi><lb/>
                paper, his object is to cut off the margins as much as possible</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>and then have them bound in smaller vols. according to his<lb/> own taste, they being
                for a very young lady who could not<lb/> well hold one of these books in her hands
                the time she should,<lb/> in consequence of the weight, the other two setts you
                will<lb/> please send according to the order enclosed, all three setts<lb/> are
                bespoken consequently they must be according to order<lb/> and those you
                    <sic>cant</sic> fulfill (if any) according to the order do<lb/> not send at all,
                as I am assured to receive them on my<lb/> hands, you would do well also to print up
                a few setts more<lb/> for me to sell with at least the Kee<add>?</add>m books
                divided,<lb/> in two or three and <del>all the</del> always on <hi rend="underline"
                    >thin</hi> paper, as these<lb/> heavy Books will not sell, the <placeName>West
                    India</placeName> ladies will<lb/> not use them the English addit<add>?</add>
                being, so much<lb/> smaller or lighter.</p>
            <p>I am very much obliged to you for the notice you took<lb/> of my dear wifes death,
                the <sic>centiments</sic> of pref<add>?</add>d being<lb/> your own I am doubly
                thankful</p>
            <p>I would surmise on the price of the Books you charge them<lb/> 5 <add>?</add> over
                your price as here 5 franc <sic>peices</sic> pass for dollars<lb/> and if you
                require <sic>remittince</sic> in that sp<add>?</add> you will have<lb/> to loose the
                diffre, however do not mention any thing of<lb/> that in your letter as I may
                    <sic>prehaps</sic> have to show<lb/> it to them—</p>
            <pb n="2R"/>
            <p>in your kind form of <date>2d May</date> I<add>?</add> recive<add>?</add> with much
                pleasure your<lb/> promise to send my sister <persName>Mrs. Luiso</persName> a
                number of the Occidents<lb/> I have written her to that effect and have requested
                her to apply<lb/> to your Agent in <placeName>London</placeName> if she does not
                hear from them—<lb/> with the sett of prayer Books herein order to be sent
                unbound<lb/> please send (on same s<add>?</add> paper and same size) a sett<lb/> of
                Pentatuch unbound as the persons <del>whiles</del> wishes<add>?</add> to have<lb/>
                them forming one complete sett, all bound alike and all<lb/> printed as he likes, I
                will copy below this the order he<lb/> has given me in his own words to avoid
                mistakes—</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">hoping you have passed pleasantly the<lb/>
                <sic>hollidays</sic> and that you may see many happy<lb/> returns of them I am Your
                Sincere friend &amp;c &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <persName role="author">M Daunt</persName>
            </p>
            <p>in your form of <date>2d March</date> you say “The books ordered by
                        <placeName>P<add>?</add> Cabello</placeName><lb/> will go by the next
                Packet, <add>?</add> I do not Re<add>?</add> having order any<lb/> books by
                        <placeName>P<add>?</add> Cabello</placeName> or any where <add>?</add> if
                you have <add>?</add> any <add>?</add><lb/> let me know.—</p>
            <p>
                <hi rend="underline">Copy</hi>
            </p>
            <p>Note</p>
            <p>One sett of prayer books<lb/> One Ditto Pentatuche}</p>
            <p>all printed on thin paper to be<lb/> unbound, the persons wants to get<lb/> them
                bound here that he may divide<lb/> them to his liking and his motive for<lb/>
                <add>?</add>ing thin paper is because he wants them<lb/> for his young daughter
                consequently wants<lb/> them light if this cant be sent according<lb/> to his desire
                do not send them—</p>
            <pb n="2V"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <addressee>Isaac Leeser Esqre.</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(center)indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
